# Kidofun Requirements Document

## 1. Application Overview

### 1.1 Application Name
Kidofun

### 1.2 Application Description
Kidofun is a mobile application designed for children under five years old, providing a collection of 50+ famous nursery rhymes with audio playback and animations. The app is designed to work offline after download, allowing children to enjoy rhymes without requiring continuous network connectivity.

### 1.3 Target Users
Children under 5 years old and their parents/guardians

## 2. Core Features
\n### 2.1 Rhyme Library
- Provide 50+ famous nursery rhymes including:
  - Twinkle Twinkle Little Star\n  - Baa Baa Black Sheep
  - Humpty Dumpty
  - Mary Had a Little Lamb
  - Old MacDonald Had a Farm
  - The Wheels on the Bus
  - Row Row Row Your Boat
  - Itsy Bitsy Spider
  - Five Little Ducks
  - Head Shoulders Knees and Toes
  - Hickory Dickory Dock
  - Jack and Jill
  - London Bridge is Falling Down\n  - Ring Around the Rosie
  - Pop Goes the Weasel
  - If You're Happy and You Know It
  - The Alphabet Song
  - Five Little Monkeys
  - Yankee Doodle
  - This Old Man
  - Three Blind Mice
  - Hot Cross Buns
  - Little Bo Peep
  - Hey Diddle Diddle
  - Pat-a-Cake
  - Rock-a-Bye Baby
  - Hush Little Baby
  - Are You Sleeping\n  - The Muffin Man
  - Sing a Song of Sixpence\n  - And 20+ more popular rhymes
- Each rhyme includes text display, audio playback, and animation
- Support offline playback after download

### 2.2 Audio Playback
- High-quality audio for each rhyme\n- Play/pause controls
- Volume adjustment
- Auto-play next rhyme option
- Repeat single rhyme option

### 2.3 Animation Features
- Engaging animations synchronized with each rhyme
- Character animations matching rhyme content
- Colorful visual effects to capture children's attention
- Simple touch-triggered animations for interactive engagement
- Smooth transitions between scenes

### 2.4 Category Organization
- Rhymes organized by categories including:
  - Animals
  - Numbers
  - Bedtime\n  - Action Songs
  - Classic Favorites
  - Learning & Education

### 2.5 Interactive Features\n- Simple touch interactions for navigation\n- Favorite rhymes marking feature
- Recently played rhymes section
- Shuffle play mode\n- Child-friendly interface design\n
## 3. Technical Requirements

### 3.1 Platform
- Mobile application (downloadable format)
- Offline functionality after initial download
- Compatible with iOS and Android devices\n
### 3.2 Content Requirements
- 50+ famous nursery rhymes with complete lyrics
- Audio files for all rhymes
- Animation assets for each rhyme
- Child-appropriate visual design
- Optimized app size for easy download

## 4. User Interface

### 4.1 Design Principles
- Simple and intuitive navigation suitable for young children
- Large, easy-to-tap buttons
- Bright, engaging colors
- Clear visual feedback for interactions
- Child-safe design with no external links or ads
- Age-appropriate font sizes and readability

### 4.2 Main Screens
- Home screen with category selection
- Rhyme list view within each category
- Individual rhyme playback screen with lyrics, audio controls, and animations
- Favorites section for quick access to preferred rhymes
- Recently played section

## 5. Additional Features

### 5.1 Parental Controls
- Simple settings menu for parents
- Volume lock option
- Timer function for usage control
- Sleep mode with automatic shutdown

### 5.2 Progress Tracking
- Track which rhymes have been played
- Visual indicators for new content
- Achievement badges for exploring different categories

### 5.3 User Experience\n- No in-app purchases
- No advertisements
- No external links to ensure child safety
- Simple onboarding tutorial for first-time users
